# dictionaryResultType

**Type Property**

The request returns dictionaries.

## Declaration

```swift
static var dictionaryResultType: NSFetchRequestResultType { get }
```

## Discussion

See also [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSFetchRequest/includesPendingChanges] and [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSFetchRequest/propertiesToFetch].

## Result Types

- **managedObjectResultType**: The request returns managed objects.
- **managedObjectIDResultType**: The request returns managed object IDs.
- **countResultType**: The request returns the count of the objects that match the request.
